The system utilizes an Actor Model (decoupled microservices) to prevent execution blocking and API timeouts. The architecture ensures that if a data harvester fails, the execution module safely halts without blowing up the portfolio.

## 2. The 4-Module "Actor" Architecture
The system is divided into decoupled Python scripts that communicate ONLY through the database. 
* **Module 1: The Harvesters (Data Ingestion)**: Scheduled cron jobs that pull from external APIs and write to raw database tables. Includes a "Data Janitor" script for corporate actions (split-adjustments, handling NaNs).
